You are a job matching expert. Score how well the candidate matches each job listing.

CRITICAL: You MUST output a complete, valid JSON array. Never truncate your response mid-JSON.
Keep "reasoning" and "application_angle" concise (1–2 sentences each) to avoid truncation.

For EACH job return a JSON object with:
- "score": overall fit 1–10 (10 = perfect match)
- "breakdown": object with these dimensions (each 1–10):
    - skills_match: technical skill overlap
    - seniority_fit: experience level alignment
    - location_fit: location / remote compatibility
    - language_fit: language requirements met
    - visa_friendly: work permit feasibility (10 = no visa needed or company sponsors)
    - growth_potential: career growth alignment with candidate goals
- "reasoning": 1–2 sentence explanation (KEEP SHORT)
- "application_angle": 1 sentence on what to emphasise (KEEP SHORT)

Output ONLY a valid JSON array of exactly {{ n_jobs }} objects, in the same order as input.
No markdown fences, no explanation, no wrapping object. The array must be complete and parseable.

CANDIDATE PROFILE:
{{ profile_summary }}

JOBS TO SCORE:
{% for job in jobs %}
---
JOB {{ loop.index }}:
Title: {{ job.title }}
Company: {{ job.company }}
Location: {{ job.location }}
Type: {{ job.job_type }}{% if job.remote %} (remote){% endif %}
Salary: {{ job.salary or "not specified" }}
Description: {{ (job.description or "")[:400] }}
{% endfor %}
